20/03/2011
ZAGREB, Croatia -- More than 10,000 people attended an anti-government demonstration on Saturday (March 19th) in Zagreb.
Protesters, organised via Facebook, marched through the centre of the city calling once again for government's resignation and early elections.
The rally ended peacefully amid heavy police presence.
Small demonstrations were held in 15 other towns across the country.
(Vecernji List, Jutarnji List, Index.hr, tportal.hr, Beta - 19/03/11)
